Sample

1st row<p>The day of parting has finally come. Milk will leave and Choco finally decided to stay. Jungwoo and Choco have a conversation that may be the last.</p>
2nd row<p>Nutty generals Bache and Gokstad come in as judges in a Christmas quiz that eliminates yet another contestant.</p>
3rd row<p>Lampje lives with her father Augustus in the lighthouse. Every evening she climbs up to light the big lamp. But one time, when there's a storm, the matches run out. The lamp stays out and in the dark night a large ship crashes against the rocks. Augustus is blamed and imprisoned for punishment. Light has to go to work in the Black House on the cliff, and everyone knows that a monster lives there. Martha, the housekeeper, forbids Lampie to go upstairs. But Lampje misses her father and the sea, and she can only see the lighthouse from the tower room. On tiptoe she sneaks up the stairs...</p>
4th row<p>The monster attacks Lampje but she is not afraid and fends off. From now on she has to take care of the fish boy, who is locked in the tower room. It is not easy what she does, and Vis thinks she is just a stupid child. Lampje is fed up with him calling her names and walks away, but she is soon sent back. The fish boy misses his father the Admiral, who is on a journey and is ashamed of his deformed son. In desperation, Pisces tries to act like an ordinary boy. Lampje wants Vis to do something for her: teach her to read. In return, Lampje takes Vis outside for the first time in his life. The two children become friends.</p>
5th row<p>Lampie takes Vis to the fair, where they meet Vis's aunt, Radiant Diamond, in a tent of Earth-Shaking Creatures. The boss of the tent sees a free attraction in Vis and tries to catch the fish boy. Radiant Diamond helps Fish escape, but does not survive. Together with the people of the fair, Lampje and Fish say goodbye to Radiant Diamond and return her to the sea. As his father the Admiral returns from his journey, Fish discovers where he comes from and overcomes his fear of water. Lampje is afraid that she will lose her new boyfriend.</p>
